name: axios
text: Mexican President Andrés Manuel López Obrador's White House visit was catnip for the Trump campaign. Campaign officials tell Axios they plan to use some of his comments to try to court Hispanic voters. https://t.co/fS28W28PpR

text:
RT @jonathanvswan: “The White House procured authorship attribution software to match Anonymous' writing style against internal writing samples from current administration officials. But the software was difficult to use and the effort failed.”

name: axios
text: JUST IN: China said it will ban entry to Sens. Marco Rubio and Ted Cruz over their criticisms of human rights abuses in Xinjiang. https://t.co/YhLW7nF6u1

name: axios
text: Roger Stone told Axios in a phone interview that he plans to write and speak for President Trump's re-election now that he "won't die in a squalid hellhole of corona-19 virus." https://t.co/Y5FHwFqfYW

name: axios
text: Maria Serda, a respiratory therapist at an HCA Healthcare hospital in Corpus Christi, Texas, told Axios that staff are limited to one N95 mask per day, and gowns are being monitored now, too. https://t.co/5X0IqKmdXL
